Bernard Madoff's massive fraud scheme has sent shockwaves across the financial world.
Despite warning signs, hedge fund companies continued to promote his funds to investors worldwide.
Major European banks like Santander and BNP Paribas face significant losses.
The scandal's impact in Spain could surpass that of Lehman Brothers' collapse.
Madoff's Ponzi scheme fooled even the most sophisticated investors, raising questions about regulatory oversight.
With losses estimated at $50 billion, the extent of the deception is staggering.
Investors are left questioning the due diligence of their advisers as they grapple with the aftermath of this unprecedented financial scandal.
